> Problem statement: 
Given an integer array nums and an integer val, remove all occurrences of val in nums in-place.

The order of elements may be changed. After removing the elements, return the number of elements k that are not equal to val.

The first k elements of nums should contain the elements not equal to val. The remaining elements are not important.

> class Solution:
    def removeElement(self, nums: List[int], val: int) -> int:
        k = 0  # pointer for position of next valid element
        
        for i in range(len(nums)):
            if nums[i] != val:
                nums[k] = nums[i]
                k += 1
        
        return k
        
